{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17538626","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17538626"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:30:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:30:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16255"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16255","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16255"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.07,0.02,0.55,0.34]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8946"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110322"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8946","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8946"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2024-11-23T19:00:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-01T13:56:19+09:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2024-11-23T19:21:47+10:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-15 14:07:45"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16255"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"13481"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92593"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2112"},{"type":"tags","id":"2320"},{"type":"tags","id":"4101"},{"type":"tags","id":"4105"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"4828"},{"type":"tags","id":"12801"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21287"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37511"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37547"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38866"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38907"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40724"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40763"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41774"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92593"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110322","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/110322"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 24-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with a three-day history of right-sided lower abdominal pain. The pain is dull and intermittent. She has regular menstrual cycles and her last period was two weeks ago. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. She is sexually active with a regular partner.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Her abdomen is soft with mild tenderness in the right iliac fossa without guarding or rebound. Bimanual examination reveals mild right adnexal tenderness without masses.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA transvaginal ultrasound shows a simple right ovarian cyst measuring 3.2 cm in diameter with thin walls, no septations, and no solid components. There is no free fluid. A pregnancy test is negative.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate management plan?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Progesterone only pill","Laparoscopic cystectomy","Diagnostic laparoscopy","Conservative management","Repeat ultrasound in 6-8 weeks"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with a simple ovarian follicular cyst, which is a common finding in women of reproductive age. The ultrasound findings are characteristic of a physiological cyst: small size, thin walls, no septations, and no solid components.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERepeat ultrasound in 6-8 weeks\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate management for simple ovarian cysts less than 5 cm in diameter in premenopausal women. Most of these cysts are functional (either follicular or corpus luteum) and will resolve spontaneously within two to three menstrual cycles. While RCOG guidelines suggest that asymptomatic simple cysts 30-50 mm in diameter do not require follow-up, this patient is symptomatic, which warrants follow-up imaging to ensure resolution of both the cyst and symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConservative management\u003C/strong\u003E alone without follow-up imaging would miss persistent cysts that may require further evaluation or intervention. Per RCOG guidelines, asymptomatic simple cysts 30-50 mm do not require follow-up, cysts 50-70 mm require ultrasound follow-up, and cysts more than 70 mm should be considered for either further imaging (MRI) or surgical intervention. However, as this patient is symptomatic, follow-up imaging is warranted regardless of cyst size.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELaparoscopic cystectomy\u003C/strong\u003E would be overly aggressive for a small, simple cyst. Surgical intervention is typically reserved for cysts that are large (\u0026gt;5-7 cm), complex, persistent, or causing severe symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProgesterone only pill\u003C/strong\u003E is not indicated as there is no evidence that it helps resolve existing cysts. While hormonal contraception may prevent new cyst formation, it does not affect existing cysts.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiagnostic laparoscopy\u003C/strong\u003E is not indicated for a simple ovarian cyst with characteristic ultrasound features. This invasive procedure would only be considered if there was diagnostic uncertainty or concern for other pathology.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Simple ovarian cysts less than 5cm in diameter typically resolve spontaneously within 2-3 menstrual cycles.","Symptomatic ovarian cysts warrant follow-up imaging regardless of size to ensure resolution.","Features of simple cysts on ultrasound include thin walls, anechoic fluid, and absence of solid components or septations."],"references":["Royal College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists. Management of suspected ovarian masses in premenopausal women (Green-top Guideline No. 62) [Internet]. London: RCOG; 2011 [cited 2024 Nov 23]. Available from: https://www.rcog.org.uk/guidance/browse-all-guidance/green-top-guidelines/ovarian-masses-in-premenopausal-women-management-of-suspected-green-top-guideline-no-62/","Bethune M. How to manage a complex ovarian cyst. O\u0026G\u202fMagazine. 2020\u202fAutumn;22(1). Available from: https://www.ogmagazine.org.au/22/1-22/how-to-manage-a-complex-ovarian-cyst/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92593"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16255"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92593","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92593"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-29T16:00:12+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-01T13:56:29+09:30","number":9,"notes":"","plagiarismCheckedAt":null,"plagiarismScore":null,"plagiarismReportUrl":null},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8946"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110322"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"12201"}},"generation":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt